The paper deals with the problem of panoptic segmentation, which is a computer vision task related to image understanding and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new framework that integrates object location information into panoptic segmentation, which involves designing sub-networks and flows to achieve this objective. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are closely related to computer vision. Additionally, the paper involves extensive experiments and evaluation of the proposed framework, which may also place it in categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
